    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">WIRELESS RAILWAYGATE MONITORING AND CONTROLLING USING WAP</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SREEDHARAN, N<br />SUBASH KANNA, S<br />VENKATACHALAM, S</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">CONTROLLING USING WAP<br />WIRELESS RAILWAYGATE MONITORING</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">7-May-2008 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P3958</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">The main aim of this project is to develop an automated railway gate for controlling and signaling using WAP. In this project IR sensors are used to find the location of the train. The sensors are fixed at the two sides (before and after 2 kilo meter) of the railway gate. If the train approaches the railway gate, the sensor senses and sends the control signal to the embedded controller and the gate gets closed automatically and similarly, if the train leaves the railway gate, the gate gets automatically opened using embedded controller.
Similarly, the same sensors are fixed in the railway station. If the train is at railway station then the sensors senses the train and the signal is sent to the embedded controller. And then embedded controller sends this information to the other station through WAP. So the passenger easily knows the train where it is and when it will come from the announcement in the station. Each information can be viewed on the Cell phone by specifying the mobile number through a modem. Also it can be viewed on other station (computer) by specifying the IP address. For this we should have an Internet connection available.
Wireless Application Protocol or WAP is an open international standard for applications that use wireless communication. Its principal application is to enable access to the internet from a mobile phone or PDA.
A WAP browser is designed to provide all the basic services of a computer based web browser but simplified to operate within the restrictions of a mobile phone. WAP is now the protocol used for the majority of the world's mobile Internet sites, known as WAP sites.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/1487">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/1487</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/1482">2008</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
